### [Joel Chapter 2](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#001.md)

[Joel 2:11](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">joe 2:11</span></span>

his army

To verse 10 ([Joe 2:10](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#010).md) inclusive the
invading army is described; at verse 11 ([Joe
2:11](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#011).md) Jehovah's army. This "army" is
described, ([Rev 19:11-18](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#011).md). The call
to repentance is based upon the Lord's promise of deliverance, ([Joe
2:12-17](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#012).md). At verses ([Joe
2:18-20](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#018).md), we have the deliverance
([Joe 2:20](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#020).md); see "Armageddon,"

(See Scofield) - ([Rev 16:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#014).md),

and kingdom blessing in verses ([Joe
2:21-27](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#021).md). Verses 28-32 ([Joe
2:28-32](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#028).md) give the outpouring of the
Spirit, and verses 29-32 ([Joe
2:29-32](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#029).md), the cosmical signs preceding
the day of the Lord.

(See Scofield) - ([Rev 19:11](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#011).md).

