[Joel 2:28](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">joe 2:28</span></span>

afterward

Compare ([Act 2:17](../../../bib/kjv/act002.htm#017).md) which gives a
specific interpretation of "afterward" (Hebrew, "Acherith", means
"latter," "last"). "Afterward" in Joel ([Joe
2:28](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#028).md) means "in the last days" (Greek,
"eschatos", and has a partial and continuous fulfilment during the "last
days" which began with the first advent of Christ ([Heb
1:2](../../../bib/kjv/heb001.htm#002).md) but the greater fulfilment awaits
the "last days" as applied to Israel.

(See Scofield) - ([Act 2:17](../../../bib/kjv/act002.htm#017).md).

